  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 17:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] HL Funding Rate Scan: No Viable Arb Opportunities\n\n**Task:** Scan HL funding rates for arb opportunities (HEARTBEAT P4: funding arb strategy).\n\n**Finding:** Funding rates are flat across all major coins:\n| Coin | Rate/8h | Annualized | Signal |\n|------|---------|------------|--------|\n| BTC | -0.0011% | -1.2% | \u2705 LOW |\n| ETH | -0.0002% | -0.3% | \u2705 LOW |\n| SOL | -0.0033% | -3.6% | \u2705 LOW |\n\n- Negative funding on BTC/ETH/SOL = shorts paying longs. Our LONG positions are collecting (tiny) funding.\n- **BLAST** is the only >15% annualized coin (-31.1%), but $1M OI = illiquid, risky for our $37 HL balance.\n- Funding arb requires >20% ann to cover fees. Market is balanced \u2014 no crowded positions to exploit.\n\n**My thinking:** Funding arb goes on the shelf. It's a strategy for: (a) extreme sentiment (F&G < 5 or > 80), (b) post-liquidation events, or (c) token-specific catalysts. Current Extreme Fear (F&G=8) should produce negative funding (shorts paying longs), but rates are mild because the selloff was orderly, not a cascade.\n\n**Decision:** No HL trades. Strategy shelved until funding rates exceed 20% annualized on liquid coins (BTC/ETH/SOL). Will re-scan weekly.\n\n## 2026-03-30 17:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Automated Daily P&L Report Generator\n\n**Task:** Build automated daily P&L report. AGENTS.md requires daily reports at ~/clawd/reports/daily-pnl-YYYY-MM-DD.md.\n\n**Built:** `scripts/daily-pnl-report.sh` \u2014 generates structured daily report with:\n- PM + HL balances (live API queries)\n- BTC price and F&G index\n- Trade count, W/L, WR%\n- Individual trade details (time, direction, price, bias, conviction, outcome)\n- Filter distribution (which filters blocked how many signals)\n\n**Test run (interim, morning session only):**\n- PM: $930.37 | HL: $366.70 | Combined: $1,297.07\n- Trades: 5 (3W/2L = 60% WR)\n- 224 YES_ONLY blocks, 886 OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS\n\n**Cron:** Updated existing 23:00 UTC cron to use new script. Will auto-generate end-of-day reports.\n\n**Decision:** Report generation automated. No more manual daily reports needed. Will update after 19h/20h session to capture full day.\n\n## 2026-03-30 16:39 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 19h Pre-Session: VWAP Logic Clarified, Regime RANGE 0/6\n\n**Task:** Prepare for 19h session. Verify regime filter and VWAP behavior.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Regime: RANGE 0/6** \u2014 consistency 0.62, range 0.76%, trend -0.19%. Choppy action (3\u2191/3\u2193). Will trade \u2705\n\n2. **VWAP misconception corrected:** I initially thought BTC below VWAP would block 19h YES trades. WRONG. The VWAP check aligns with BIAS direction (not bet direction):\n   - Negative bias + price below VWAP \u2192 `(not bullish AND not above_vwap)` = **VWAP AGREES \u2705**\n   - The relaxation at 11h/12h only helps when price is ABOVE VWAP with negative bias (contradictory signals)\n   \n3. **19h conditions:** BTC $67,352, VWAP ~$67,573. Price below VWAP = agrees with negative bias. If bias stays negative, 19h will fire YES trades with VWAP agreement.\n\n4. **19h edge is bias-driven*",
